File: Andrey Rublev in action at last year's Wimbledon. AFP/Adrian Dennis BELGRADE - Russian tennis player Andrey Rublev has described the banning of Belarusian and Russian players as discrimination. The number 10-ranked player has said the reasons are null and void. Rublev's comments to the AFP news agency came after the 24-year-old won 4-6 7-6 (7-1) 6-2 against Czech opponent, Jiri Lehecka at the Serbia Open. Just after the invasion of Ukraine, the Russian signed 'no war please' on the lens of a camera at the Dubai Tennis Championship, showing his solitude with the people of Ukraine He maintains that the Wimbledon decision shows hatred and intolerance.